The paper deals with numerical algorithms for computing the nonlinear Fourier transform, which is a mathematical tool used in various applications such as information transmission in optical fiber. This makes it likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Signal Processing (cs.SP), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses extensions of the results to other evolution equations, which could potentially place it in the Scientific Computing (cs.SC) sub-category.
